@startuml sequence-tts-export
!theme plain
title TTS Export — Tabletop Simulator Deck Export

actor User
participant "DeckDetailPage" as Detail
participant "DeckActions" as Actions
participant "api.ts" as API
participant "tts-export.php" as TTS
participant "scryfall-cache.php" as Scryfall
database "MySQL" as DB

User -> Detail : View deck detail
User -> Actions : Click "Export to TTS"

Actions -> API : api.exportToTTS(deckId)
API -> TTS : GET /tts-export?deck_id=X

TTS -> DB : SELECT lc.card_name, lc.quantity, lc.is_commander\nFROM list_cards lc\nJOIN lists l ON l.id = lc.list_id\nWHERE l.deck_id = ?
DB --> TTS : ListCard[] with scryfall data

loop Each card in deck
  TTS -> Scryfall : Lookup cached card data\n(image URLs, DFC status)
  Scryfall --> TTS : Card image URL, back face URL

  opt Double-Faced Card
    TTS -> TTS : Track front + back faces\nseparately for montage
  end
end

TTS -> TTS : Build multi-sheet montage\n(10x7 grid per sheet)\nCalculate orientation per card
TTS -> TTS : Generate TTS JSON object:\n- DeckIDs[]\n- CustomDeck{} with sheet URLs\n- ContainedObjects[] per card\n- Transform positions

TTS --> API : {tts_object JSON}
API --> Actions : Download TTS save file

note right of TTS
  Output is a TTS Saved Object JSON
  Import via Tabletop Simulator
  Saved Objects folder
  Supports 70 cards per sheet
  Handles DFCs with separate back sheet
end note

@enduml

' ============================================================

@startuml sequence-rules-guru
!theme plain
title Rules Guru — AI Rules Chat Flow

actor User
participant "RulesChatPage" as Chat
participant "api.ts" as API
participant "rules/chat.php" as RulesChat
participant "rules/patterns.php" as Patterns
participant "rules/active-game.php" as ActiveGame
participant "rules/conversations.php" as Convos
database "MySQL" as DB

== Context-Aware Entry ==
opt From active game
  User -> Chat : Open Rules Guru during live game
  Chat -> API : api.getRulesActiveGame(sessionCode)
  API -> ActiveGame : GET /rules/active-game?code=X
  ActiveGame -> DB : SELECT current game state\n(commanders, board state)
  DB --> ActiveGame : GameContext
  ActiveGame --> API : {players[], commanders[], phase}
  API --> Chat : Pre-load game context
end

== Ask a Question ==
User -> Chat : "Can I respond to a board wipe\nwith my Teferi's Protection?"
Chat -> API : api.sendRulesQuestion(convId, question, context)
API -> RulesChat : POST /rules/chat

RulesChat -> DB : Load conversation history
DB --> RulesChat : Prior messages[]

RulesChat -> RulesChat : Build context:\n- MTG Comprehensive Rules\n- Relevant pattern knowledge\n- Active game state (if any)\n- Conversation history

RulesChat -> Patterns : Lookup matching patterns
Patterns -> DB : SELECT patterns\nWHERE keywords MATCH
DB --> Patterns : RelevantPattern[]
Patterns --> RulesChat : Pattern context

RulesChat -> RulesChat : Call AI with full context\nGenerate rules-accurate answer
RulesChat -> DB : INSERT question + answer
DB --> RulesChat : ok
RulesChat --> API : {answer, rules_refs[], confidence}
API --> Chat : Display answer with rule citations

opt Rate Answer
  User -> Chat : Rate answer quality
  Chat -> API : api.rateRulesAnswer(id, rating)
  API -> RulesChat : PUT /rules/qa-log-rate
  RulesChat -> DB : UPDATE rating
end

== Conversation History ==
User -> Chat : View past conversations
Chat -> API : api.getRulesConversations()
API -> Convos : GET /rules/conversations
Convos -> DB : SELECT conversations\nORDER BY updated_at DESC
DB --> Convos : Conversation[]
Convos --> API : conversation list
API --> Chat : Display conversation history

@enduml

